OL,3,CChildren's hospice fears for its
OL,4,Cfuture over National Insurance hike
OL,6,FA hospice charity, which supports
OL,7,Fvulnerable children in Dorset and
OL,8,FWiltshire, says it may have to
OL,9,Frestrict its services unless the
OL,10,Fgovernment reverses plans to increase
OL,11,Femployers' National Insurance.
OL,13,FJulia's House has been providing
OL,14,Fessential day and residential respite
OL,15,Fcare for the most seriously ill
OL,16,Fchildren for 20 years.
OL,18,FIts annual budget is #10 million and
OL,19,F90% of that comes from fundraising.
