OL,3,CChildren's hospice fears for its
OL,4,Cfuture over National Insurance hike
OL,6,FA government spokesperson said: "We
OL,7,Fwant everyone to have access to high-
OL,8,Fquality end of life care and are aware
OL,9,Fof the financial pressures facing the
OL,10,Fhospice sector, and of the huge
OL,11,Fgenerosity of the British public,
OL,12,Fwhose donations provide a significant
OL,13,Fproportion of hospice funding.
OL,15,F"We are determined to shift more
OL,16,Fhealthcare into the community and
OL,17,Fensure patients and their families
OL,18,Freceive high-quality, personalised
OL,19,Fcare in the most appropriate setting,
OL,20,Fand hospices will have a big role to
OL,21,Fplay in that shift."
